WEBVTT

00:08.747 --> 00:10.662
Woman: Personal assistant
Olivia McLeland.

00:10.706 --> 00:12.795
Man: ...after being accused of
killing her reality star boss

00:12.838 --> 00:14.666
Hayley Halliwell.
- With a fatal dose of heroin...

00:14.710 --> 00:17.930
...as we begin the fifth day of
the celebrity trial of the year.

00:17.974 --> 00:19.062
♪ ...notes♪

00:19.106 --> 00:21.064
♪ In the lights and smoke♪

00:21.108 --> 00:23.327
Your Honor, the defense moves
for an immediate dismissal.

00:23.371 --> 00:26.548
1118.1.
No reasonable jury could...

00:26.591 --> 00:28.985
Your Honor, these theatrics
are making a complete mockery

00:29.029 --> 00:30.639
of what's been going on...
- Theatrics? Prosecution rested.

00:30.682 --> 00:32.293
Their evidence
was woefully inadequate.

00:32.336 --> 00:34.686
Video evidence of the defendant
purchasing heroin,

00:34.730 --> 00:37.167
M.E.'s testimony that the victim
had been forcibly injected

00:37.211 --> 00:39.996
with said heroin.
- We've heard it. We were here.

00:40.040 --> 00:43.652
My point is--Judge, if Mr. Pryce isn't keen
on letting the jury decide

00:43.695 --> 00:46.089
what's going on...Mr. Pryce is keen
on saving time, Your Honor.

00:46.133 --> 00:48.744
Give you a day off.
A little spa time, maybe.

00:48.787 --> 00:50.398
[ thud ][ exhales deeply ]

00:52.443 --> 00:55.968
I'm touched, counselor,
but the motion is denied.

00:56.012 --> 00:57.231
We're going to take a recess,

00:57.274 --> 00:58.841
and when we come back,
the jury will return,

00:58.884 --> 01:00.190
and the defense
will present their case.

01:00.234 --> 01:01.800
[ gavel bangs ]All rise.

01:06.675 --> 01:10.461
[ gallery murmuring ]

01:12.811 --> 01:14.117
[ door closes ]

01:14.161 --> 01:16.206
[ indistinct conversations ]

01:16.250 --> 01:17.468
Thomas, you worried?

01:17.512 --> 01:18.861
Think you've done enough
to get a conviction?

01:18.904 --> 01:20.645
- No comment.
- See, this is what happens.

01:20.689 --> 01:24.258
- Every word he says they print.
- It's gonna get worse.

01:24.301 --> 01:26.651
Murdered TV star.
Famous defense lawyer.

01:26.695 --> 01:28.914
Armchair quarterback's
telling me how to try my case.

01:28.958 --> 01:31.047
Justice for Hayley!
Justice for Hayley!

01:31.091 --> 01:33.005
You did your job, boss.
Nailed it.

01:33.049 --> 01:34.964
Evidence was clear.
It's a slam dunk.

01:35.007 --> 01:37.140
Just keep Pryce
from muddying the waters.

01:37.184 --> 01:39.316
Thank you, Callan. I'd be
lost without your guidance.

01:39.360 --> 01:41.536
I'm just saying
he's gonna be shameless.

01:41.579 --> 01:43.277
Hold the line.

01:43.320 --> 01:44.756
Hayley's mother.

01:44.800 --> 01:47.411
I can't believe
she has to go through this.

01:47.455 --> 01:49.152
I'd better check in.

01:49.196 --> 01:50.936
You want to be useful?
Just tell me

01:50.980 --> 01:53.287
Judge Carmichael knows
Pryce is full of it, right?

01:53.330 --> 01:55.550
Thomas, I am not
the Lola Whisperer.

01:55.593 --> 01:57.029
[ cellphone rings ]

01:57.073 --> 02:00.729
Take that call.
Check in later.

02:00.772 --> 02:02.774
Mark: This place is a circus.

02:02.818 --> 02:04.167
Lola: Have you seen
this crazy article?

02:04.211 --> 02:05.516
Yeah. Ria sent me the link.

02:05.560 --> 02:07.823
- It's so bizarre.
- You are fierce and fabulous.

02:07.866 --> 02:10.086
[ elevator bell dings ]You make even your judicial
robes look glamorous.

02:10.130 --> 02:11.522
They did get that part right.

02:11.566 --> 02:13.872
I caught Pryce's little performance just now.

02:13.916 --> 02:15.483
He's testing you.
He's been lying in the reeds

02:15.526 --> 02:17.049
all through
the prosecution's case.

02:17.093 --> 02:18.094
- I know what he's doing.
- That's why he didn't

02:18.138 --> 02:19.748
give his opening.
He's saving it.

02:19.791 --> 02:21.619
Are you mansplaining
my trial to me?

02:21.663 --> 02:23.055
I'm just--It's a tactic.

02:23.099 --> 02:25.101
He's gonna use the spotlight
to put pressure on you.

02:25.145 --> 02:26.885
It won't work.
A woman was killed.

02:26.929 --> 02:28.713
Another woman's freedom
is at stake.

02:28.757 --> 02:30.106
I know what my job is.

02:30.150 --> 02:33.109
All I'm saying is do not
underestimate this guy.

02:33.153 --> 02:34.937
Sherri:
You need to contain him.

02:34.980 --> 02:36.199
Got to go.

02:36.243 --> 02:38.245
You need to set
boundaries for Pryce.

02:38.288 --> 02:41.857
- Seriously? You, too?
- He needs to follow the rules.

02:41.900 --> 02:43.250
Judge Benner wants
to see you.

02:43.293 --> 02:45.077
I'll tell her
you're on your way.

02:45.121 --> 02:47.558
I can handle Adam Pryce.

02:50.257 --> 02:52.128
On my way.
My hearing ran late.

02:52.172 --> 02:54.957
I'll be three minutes.
Do not talk to anyone, Billy.

02:55.000 --> 02:56.393
Just sit quietly in the hall
until I get there.

02:56.437 --> 02:58.787
If they offer you coffee,
that's fine,

02:58.830 --> 03:01.224
but nothing else. Oh, come on.

03:01.268 --> 03:04.445
- Up or down?
- Up. DA's office. Hi.

03:04.488 --> 03:06.969
Hi. I know a shortcut.

03:07.012 --> 03:09.624
You are seriously the best.

03:09.667 --> 03:11.539
[ knock on door ]

03:11.582 --> 03:14.106
Apparently, you've got
style and substance.

03:14.150 --> 03:16.457
I am, for the record,
mortified.

03:16.500 --> 03:18.285
You wanted to see me?

03:18.328 --> 03:22.114
Yes. You have a friend...
Briana Turner?

03:22.158 --> 03:25.030
Bree? Yeah. She was
my college roommate. Why?

03:25.074 --> 03:28.251
My assistant found this,
#JudgeLola.

03:28.295 --> 03:30.297
Che Guevara
is one of your heroes?

03:30.340 --> 03:32.473
He was in college.
The media have this?

03:32.516 --> 03:34.083
Not yet, but they will.

03:34.126 --> 03:36.999
I remember this party.
It was fun.

03:37.042 --> 03:40.568
I am the last person
you will ever say that to.

03:40.611 --> 03:43.179
Okay.How are you?

03:43.223 --> 03:46.835
- I want my courthouse back.
- No. I mean how areyou?

03:46.878 --> 03:49.403
Oh. Right.

03:49.446 --> 03:52.536
If this is about my breakup,
please don't.

03:52.580 --> 03:54.277
Apologies. I'll call Bree

03:54.321 --> 03:56.323
and have her
take this picture down.

03:56.366 --> 03:59.021
I'm a little shaky sometimes,
which is just weird.

03:59.064 --> 04:02.938
Mornings are the worst,
but...I'm fine.

04:02.981 --> 04:05.114
Thank you for asking.

04:05.157 --> 04:07.116
Anytime you want to talk,
I'm just down the hall.

04:09.074 --> 04:12.556
Any other...
fun college snapshots

04:12.600 --> 04:14.123
coming our way?

04:14.166 --> 04:16.604
I think we'll just
have to wait and see.

04:16.647 --> 04:20.042
♪♪♪

04:20.085 --> 04:22.174
This is my favorite piece.

04:22.218 --> 04:23.959
I think you're gonna love it,
and I think it'll be...

04:24.002 --> 04:26.614
Adam Pryce.
Read all his books.

04:26.657 --> 04:28.355
Yeah, we've been studying
his cases in Trial Ad.

04:28.398 --> 04:30.879
Hmm.[ elevator bell dings,
gate opens ]

04:30.922 --> 04:34.230
Cassie: [ whispers ]
Here she comes.

04:34.274 --> 04:36.493
Pryce: Olivia,
come see what Cassie brought

04:36.537 --> 04:40.323
for you to wear today.
What do you think?That was Olivia McLeland?

04:40.367 --> 04:42.543
She looks nothing
like she does on the news.

04:42.586 --> 04:44.327
Yeah, Pryce brought in
a personal stylist--

04:44.371 --> 04:46.677
clothes, makeup,
the whole thing.Really? That's insane.

04:46.721 --> 04:48.418
Like you wouldn't do
the same for your clients

04:48.462 --> 04:50.246
if you had the budget.

04:50.290 --> 04:52.248
Thank you for this.
I owe you.

04:52.292 --> 04:54.076
I'm gonna take you
for pie tonight.

04:54.119 --> 04:56.600
- You like pie, right?
- I love pie.

04:56.644 --> 04:59.255
- Like, I lovepie.
- [ laughs ]

04:59.299 --> 05:02.389
Yet unbelievably, I have
to study. Exams next week.

05:02.432 --> 05:04.216
- Raincheck?
- You have flashcards?

05:04.260 --> 05:05.783
- No.
- No?

05:05.827 --> 05:09.570
Oh, you're gonna need
flashcards, like, stat.

05:09.613 --> 05:10.614
Thanks!

05:10.658 --> 05:20.798
[ indistinct conversations ]

05:20.842 --> 05:22.278
[ laughter ]

05:22.322 --> 05:25.455
This is seriously
the most crazy I've seen it.

05:25.499 --> 05:29.677
[ gasps ] Cassie Lange,
the stylist to the stars.

05:29.720 --> 05:31.766
Her Insta is a must-follow.

05:31.809 --> 05:33.594
You're really
into this stuff.

05:33.637 --> 05:36.074
Guilty pleasure.

05:36.118 --> 05:38.207
Let's go. Judge is ready.

05:38.250 --> 05:39.382
Woman: Cassie!

05:39.426 --> 05:41.210
[ indistinct conversations ]

05:41.253 --> 05:43.125
Woman: Here she is.Woman: Oh, my God.
Olivia's back. Oh, my God.

05:43.168 --> 05:45.170
- Woman: Here she is.
- Woman: Oh, my God.

05:45.214 --> 05:47.129
Woman: She looks amazing.

05:47.172 --> 05:48.739
Man: What is she wearing?

05:48.783 --> 05:49.871
Woman: She looks amazing.

05:49.914 --> 05:51.873
♪♪♪

05:51.916 --> 05:54.397
All rise.

05:54.441 --> 05:56.921
Department 61 of
the Los Angeles Superior Court

05:56.965 --> 05:58.227
is now in session.

05:58.270 --> 06:00.360
The Honorable
Lola Carmichael presiding.

06:00.403 --> 06:03.450
Please take your seats.
Let's bring the jury in.

06:03.493 --> 06:06.975
We are back on the record
in People v. McLeland.

06:07.018 --> 06:08.629
Those of you in the gallery,

06:08.672 --> 06:11.806
I expect you to continue
to behave yourselves.

06:11.849 --> 06:15.418
This room is a church,
a temple of justice.

06:15.462 --> 06:18.639
Remain seated and silent.
Phones off and out of sight.

06:18.682 --> 06:22.382
No texting. No photos.
Mr. Pryce, you may proceed.

06:24.819 --> 06:29.606
Olivia McLeland is not, uh...

06:29.650 --> 06:32.348
I'm sorry. I can't believe
what I just heard.

06:32.392 --> 06:35.003
A temple of justice.

06:35.046 --> 06:37.701
Ladies and gentlemen,
justice has left the building.

06:37.745 --> 06:40.356
Careful, Mr. Pryce.

06:40.400 --> 06:42.967
For a week, we have been hearing

06:43.011 --> 06:46.449
that Olivia is a thief,
a killer!

06:46.493 --> 06:49.278
Who on earth
are they talking about?

06:49.321 --> 06:53.021
Olivia was loyal
to her employer Hayley.

06:53.064 --> 06:55.415
Justice has left the building,
but I am going to bring it back

06:55.458 --> 07:00.115
because Olivia McLeland
didn't kill anyone.

07:00.158 --> 07:01.377
Man: That's right.
Free Olivia!

07:01.421 --> 07:03.335
Crowd: Free Olivia! Free Olivia!
Free Olivia!

07:03.379 --> 07:06.991
- Backup.
- Order! Sit down!

07:07.035 --> 07:09.472
- [ shouting continues ]
- Now!

07:09.516 --> 07:10.778
[ gavel banging ]Come to order!

07:10.821 --> 07:12.954
[ shouting continues,
gavel continues banging ]

07:12.997 --> 07:16.348
This isn't happening.
This isn't happening.Lola: Everyone, sit down!

07:16.392 --> 07:18.481
[ shouting continues ]

07:18.525 --> 07:21.049
Order![ gavel banging ]

07:21.092 --> 07:25.619
[ shouting continues ]

07:33.540 --> 07:36.673
♪♪♪

07:36.717 --> 07:37.935
I don't know, man.
Depends on what happens

07:37.979 --> 07:39.415
in the off season.
If we lose Kopitar...

07:39.459 --> 07:42.462
Billy, what did I tell you?
Do not talk to anyone.

07:42.505 --> 07:43.941
- Ms. Lopez.
- Relax.

07:43.985 --> 07:46.204
We were just talking hockey.
Billy is a big Kings fan.

07:46.248 --> 07:48.032
- He didn't mention the case?
- How long have you known me?

07:48.076 --> 07:49.817
Did he ask you anything
at all?

07:49.860 --> 07:51.166
Three years,
and in all that time,

07:51.209 --> 07:52.515
have I ever given--
- In all that time,

07:52.559 --> 07:54.474
you've shown a willingness
to win at any cost.

07:54.517 --> 07:57.999
Billy Webb, PC 211--
robbery in the second degree.

07:58.042 --> 07:59.609
I have good news.

07:59.653 --> 08:00.871
We're listening.

08:00.915 --> 08:02.351
I've been authorized
to reduce the charges.

08:02.394 --> 08:04.048
Grand theft.
Three years probation,

08:04.092 --> 08:05.659
one year in County
if, Billy, you give us

08:05.702 --> 08:07.443
the location
of the stolen goods.

08:07.487 --> 08:10.272
Yeah, I can do that.Quiet, Billy. Maybe.
Maybe he can do that.

08:10.315 --> 08:13.318
And if Billy will testify
against his cousins.Benny and Kenny?

08:13.362 --> 08:15.146
You want him to flip
on his family for that?

08:15.190 --> 08:18.323
Unh-unh. No way.One year instead of five,
County instead of State.

08:18.367 --> 08:19.847
He'll be out
in a couple of months

08:19.890 --> 08:21.849
without a strike on his record.
- Full immunity, Callan.

08:21.892 --> 08:23.111
- Drop all the charges.
- We all know

08:23.154 --> 08:25.243
Benny and Kenny are
the real bad guys here,

08:25.287 --> 08:28.333
but your client was the lookout.
That means he was complicit.

08:28.377 --> 08:30.074
Full cooperation
or no deal.

08:30.118 --> 08:32.424
It's a good offer,
Ms. Lopez.

08:32.468 --> 08:34.949
[ indistinct conversations,
telephone ringing in distance ]

08:34.992 --> 08:37.517
Lola: I hope I don't need to
remind you of the stakes here.

08:37.560 --> 08:40.302
If either of you show
this court any disrespect,

08:40.345 --> 08:41.825
I will place you in contempt.
Are we clear?

08:41.869 --> 08:43.044
- Of course.
- Crystal.

08:43.087 --> 08:46.787
And, if I may, Your Honor,
well said.

08:46.830 --> 08:49.529
We're all ears, Mr. Pryce.

08:52.227 --> 08:54.011
Ladies and gentlemen
of the jury,

08:54.055 --> 08:55.839
the prosecution claims

08:55.883 --> 08:58.712
that my client killed her boss
with a fatal dose of heroin

08:58.755 --> 09:01.845
after Hayley caught her
stealing.

09:01.889 --> 09:03.630
The evidence
will show otherwise.

09:03.673 --> 09:04.935
The evidence will show that

09:04.979 --> 09:08.722
the real victim
in this case is Olivia,

09:08.765 --> 09:13.161
the victim of an abusive
drug addict, Hayley Halliwell.

09:13.204 --> 09:14.641
- [ gallery gasps and murmurs ]
- Shocking, I know.

09:14.684 --> 09:17.687
We all watched the show.
We all loved Hayley,

09:17.731 --> 09:18.993
but we didn't know her.

09:19.036 --> 09:21.212
We shouldn't punish my client
because she did.

09:21.256 --> 09:23.650
Objection.
Improper argument.

09:23.693 --> 09:25.869
Sustained. Stick
to the evidence, Mr. Pryce.

09:25.913 --> 09:27.610
Happily, Your Honor.

09:27.654 --> 09:30.308
The evidence will show
that Hayley Halliwell

09:30.352 --> 09:32.223
was an inveterate
drug user.

09:32.267 --> 09:34.138
The evidence will show
that Hayley Halliwell

09:34.182 --> 09:37.489
was an abusive employer.
The evidence will show...

09:38.969 --> 09:40.667
Emily: Are you nervous?

09:40.710 --> 09:42.538
I keep thinking Benny and Kenny
are gonna come out

09:42.582 --> 09:44.584
to kick my ass.
- They won't. You know why?

09:44.627 --> 09:46.498
- They're in custody?
- It's a good deal, Billy.

09:46.542 --> 09:48.892
All right. The search warrant
is on site.

09:48.936 --> 09:50.198
[ indistinct conversations ]

09:50.241 --> 09:51.852
Show me where
the stolen goods are.

09:51.895 --> 09:53.201
Yeah. Over here
in this cabinet.

09:53.244 --> 09:55.551
That was an uncharacteristically
generous deal

09:55.595 --> 09:57.074
you offered my client.

09:57.118 --> 09:58.815
Have you met
Benny and Kenny?

09:58.859 --> 10:00.861
You just like
saying their names.

10:00.904 --> 10:02.427
That should be
everything.

10:02.471 --> 10:05.648
[ police radio chatter,
tires screeching ]

10:05.692 --> 10:08.390
Who the hell is this?

10:09.913 --> 10:11.872
[ engine idling ]

10:11.915 --> 10:13.395
[ engine stops ]Man: Hold on!
What we got here?

10:16.528 --> 10:18.139
What the hell
is going on here?!

10:18.182 --> 10:19.575
Whoa.
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

10:19.619 --> 10:21.185
Don't know what
my dumbass grandson told you,

10:21.229 --> 10:23.187
but this is my property.
- Ma'am, we have a warrant.

10:23.231 --> 10:25.059
You've got to be ki--

10:25.102 --> 10:27.670
Billy, I'm gonna
kick your ass!Whoa. Hey.

10:27.714 --> 10:29.803
Helping the cops
against your own family?!

10:29.846 --> 10:32.109
- I raised you better!
- Ma'am, get back in the truck.

10:32.153 --> 10:33.545
If not, we'll have you
arrested for obstruction.

10:33.589 --> 10:35.156
Whatever kind of deal you cut...Ma'am, ma'am.

10:35.199 --> 10:38.463
...this won't go unanswered!
Don't think you're safe in jail!

10:38.507 --> 10:40.596
Male officer: All right, ma'am,
just get in the car, please.

10:40.640 --> 10:42.119
- This is the grandmother?
- Get in the car.

10:42.163 --> 10:43.555
Unbelievable.

10:43.599 --> 10:45.775
[ police radio chatter ]

10:45.819 --> 10:51.302
[ indistinct conversations,
cash register beeping ]

10:51.346 --> 10:53.130
Olivia's sweater
last Friday?

10:53.174 --> 10:55.916
That shade of green--
was that jade?

10:55.959 --> 10:58.048
- Celadon.
- Oh, love it.

10:58.092 --> 11:00.311
Like celery but better.
[ chuckles ]

11:00.355 --> 11:02.574
- You're the...
- The court reporter.

11:02.618 --> 11:04.098
Sara Castillo.

11:04.141 --> 11:07.449
I've been here every day.
Seen every outfit.

11:07.492 --> 11:08.798
Nice work.

11:08.842 --> 11:12.323
Thanks. Means the world to me.

11:12.367 --> 11:14.151
How exactly
do you get the gig

11:14.195 --> 11:16.153
of dressing
an accused murderer?

11:16.197 --> 11:17.502
Does it pay well,
at least?

11:17.546 --> 11:20.114
In the last week
I've had 2,000 new follows.

11:20.157 --> 11:21.942
I'm not doing it
for a short-term paycheck.

11:21.985 --> 11:24.161
I'm doing it for my brand.

11:24.205 --> 11:34.215
♪♪♪

11:34.258 --> 11:35.520
I need your help
with something.

11:35.564 --> 11:36.957
Are you gonna get me
in trouble?

11:37.000 --> 11:39.786
No. But don't mention it
to Sherri.

11:39.829 --> 11:41.613
Oh, my God.

11:41.657 --> 11:43.006
An old friend posted it
on Twitter.

11:43.050 --> 11:45.530
- I love this photo!
- I got her to take it down.

11:45.574 --> 11:47.663
I need to be sure the media
hasn't picked this up.

11:47.707 --> 11:49.970
Oh. You've come
to the right woman.

11:50.013 --> 11:51.275
You're always sending me

11:51.319 --> 11:52.755
those cute animal videos
from the 'gram.

11:52.799 --> 11:55.366
I figured I'd put that
social media savvy to use.

11:55.410 --> 11:59.022
Wow. #LIVFREE, the hashtag
for Olivia's fans?

11:59.066 --> 12:01.895
- It's taking off.
- I don't get it.

12:01.938 --> 12:04.114
How does a personal assistant
have so many fans?

12:04.158 --> 12:06.247
It's like how Kim K.
started out

12:06.290 --> 12:07.509
as Paris's stylist.

12:07.552 --> 12:10.077
Olivia was on
Hayley's reality series,

12:10.120 --> 12:12.209
plus she Instagrammed
everything Hayley did.

12:12.253 --> 12:14.385
She has, like,
2 million followers.

12:14.429 --> 12:16.387
- [ exhales deeply ]
- Can I tell you my theory?

12:16.431 --> 12:17.693
Sure.

12:17.737 --> 12:19.913
Adam Pryce is trying
to use those followers to--

12:19.956 --> 12:21.262
Ahem.
If you're about to have

12:21.305 --> 12:22.829
a third party discussion
of a case, don't.

12:22.872 --> 12:25.483
I'm listening to every word.

12:25.527 --> 12:27.050
Carmichael?

12:27.094 --> 12:28.573
Pryce: It is my duty,
and I cannot let any...

12:28.617 --> 12:30.140
You need to see this.
[ sighs ]

12:30.184 --> 12:32.752
- This is live. He's outside.
- ...get in my way.

12:32.795 --> 12:34.579
Look, I've spent
some time in courtrooms,

12:34.623 --> 12:37.017
and I--I'm fine
with being silenced,

12:37.060 --> 12:40.150
but not at the expense
of a fair trial for my client.

12:40.194 --> 12:42.413
He is trying this case
in the press.

12:42.457 --> 12:43.806
I'm not gonna stand by
and watch

12:43.850 --> 12:45.068
as justice is muzzled.

12:45.112 --> 12:47.201
He did not just say that.

12:47.244 --> 12:49.420
The jury won't--
They're on a news blackout.

12:49.464 --> 12:51.509
They have phones.
It'll seep through.

12:51.553 --> 12:53.250
I'm gonna do everything
I can do

12:53.294 --> 12:54.774
to put the facts
on the record.

12:54.817 --> 12:57.428
Your Honor, he is creating
a narrative.

12:57.472 --> 12:58.865
I know what he's doing.
I need people to stop

12:58.908 --> 13:01.258
telling me what he's doing.
- If you don't stop him,

13:01.302 --> 13:02.520
you're gonna have to
sequester the jury.

13:02.564 --> 13:03.957
That is a headache
to be avoided.

13:04.000 --> 13:06.220
I'm not gonna get into
a fistfight with Adam Pryce.

13:06.263 --> 13:08.439
I need to focus on my job,

13:08.483 --> 13:10.877
making sure the jury hears
the evidence.

13:12.966 --> 13:14.054
Sherri.

13:14.097 --> 13:16.665
Take a breath.

13:16.708 --> 13:18.623
[ wheezes ]

13:21.670 --> 13:23.628
Can we please
just get Grandma out of here?

13:23.672 --> 13:25.805
- Charge her with something.
- She's a senior citizen.

13:25.848 --> 13:27.458
Who cares?
It's felony intimidation.

13:27.502 --> 13:29.286
Since when are you
so tough on crime?

13:29.330 --> 13:32.115
Look at him.
He's terrified.

13:32.159 --> 13:34.596
She reminds me
of Ria's mother.

13:34.639 --> 13:36.293
Met the parents.

13:36.337 --> 13:38.295
Yeah. Uh, once.

13:38.339 --> 13:39.775
Getting serious?

13:39.819 --> 13:41.951
Could be headed that way,
yeah.

13:41.995 --> 13:43.953
Such a romantic.

13:43.997 --> 13:45.346
I'm just being...

13:45.389 --> 13:47.391
We haven't been together
that long.

13:47.435 --> 13:49.611
Do you know what percent
of marriages end in divorce?

13:49.654 --> 13:51.134
I do. Yeah.

13:51.178 --> 13:54.137
- Right. Of course. Right. You--
- Yeah.

13:54.181 --> 13:56.748
I'm always curious
how people...

13:56.792 --> 13:58.359
When did you know
you picked the wrong guy?

13:58.402 --> 14:01.405
When he hit me.

14:01.449 --> 14:04.669
I'm...I'm so sorry.

14:04.713 --> 14:07.324
We're done over here.
We found everything.

14:07.368 --> 14:10.893
Great. Let's go
before she comes after us.

14:10.937 --> 14:13.461
Pryce: How did you know
the deceased?

14:13.504 --> 14:15.506
We were friends.
We hung out.

14:15.550 --> 14:18.205
Hung out, Mr. Fulmer?
Were there drugs involved?

14:18.248 --> 14:20.294
Yeah. [ sighs ]
We'd be out by the pool,

14:20.337 --> 14:22.513
and there'd be, you know,
coke, Molly, whatever.

14:22.557 --> 14:24.167
[ scoffs ]
I mean, it's L.A., right?

14:24.211 --> 14:25.690
What about heroin?

14:25.734 --> 14:28.041
Did you ever witness
Hayley using heroin?Uh-huh.

14:28.084 --> 14:29.956
Would you call her
a heroin addict?

14:29.999 --> 14:31.740
Objection.
The witness is not an expert.

14:31.783 --> 14:34.003
Your Honor, I'm just
trying to ascertain--Both of you.

14:34.047 --> 14:35.178
[ man clears throat ]

14:35.222 --> 14:37.441
Saw you on the news, Mr. Pryce.

14:37.485 --> 14:39.269
You're not doing yourself
any favors.

14:39.313 --> 14:40.880
My First Amendment rights,
Your Honor.

14:40.923 --> 14:43.056
Don't give you license
to misrepresent this court.Noted.

14:43.099 --> 14:45.928
- As to the pending objection--
- You're walking a fine line.

14:45.972 --> 14:47.930
Stay on the right side of it.

14:49.366 --> 14:52.108
Objection is overruled.
The witness will answer.

14:52.152 --> 14:55.938
- She was into heroin. Yeah.
- Thank you, Mr. Fulmer.

14:55.982 --> 14:59.507
Now, um, if you would
look at the screen.

15:00.769 --> 15:03.206
- Oh, Hayley.
- Who is in this video?

15:03.250 --> 15:05.730
Objection! Your Honor, this is
the first I'm seeing this.

15:05.774 --> 15:07.341
The defense can't just
spring new evidence...

15:07.384 --> 15:09.038
- Turn off that screen.
- I thought this was deleted.

15:09.082 --> 15:11.258
- We just recovered the file.
- Stop talking.

15:11.301 --> 15:13.521
[ sobs ]

15:13.564 --> 15:15.740
[ gallery murmuring ]

15:15.784 --> 15:19.396
♪♪♪

15:19.440 --> 15:21.616
Take it easy. Take it easy.

15:21.659 --> 15:24.401
Olivia: Oh, Hayley.
Are you okay?

15:24.445 --> 15:26.577
Are you filming me?

15:26.621 --> 15:29.711
Give it to me. Give me that! Give me that! Give--

15:29.754 --> 15:31.495
[ keyboard clicks ]It's Olivia filming.

15:31.539 --> 15:33.889
He had this all along,
but he knew if he disclosed,

15:33.933 --> 15:35.412
Choi would have filed
a motion to exclude.

15:35.456 --> 15:37.197
Which you would have
granted.

15:37.240 --> 15:38.459
This doesn't prove
anything new.

15:38.502 --> 15:39.851
He's trying
to prejudice the jury

15:39.895 --> 15:42.245
by painting Olivia
as the victim.

15:42.289 --> 15:43.768
He's trying
to force your hand.

15:43.812 --> 15:45.770
If you exclude it
now that everyone--

15:45.814 --> 15:47.337
that the media
knows it exists--

15:47.381 --> 15:49.122
I know what he's doing, Sherri.I'm saying--My point is--

15:49.165 --> 15:50.297
I know what your point is,
Sherri.

15:50.340 --> 15:51.776
What's going on with you?

15:51.820 --> 15:54.605
Why are you letting this
lawyer get under your skin?

15:54.649 --> 15:56.085
Your Honor, I don't think
you're sufficiently scared.

15:56.129 --> 15:58.392
That's because I have
nothing to be afraid of.

15:58.435 --> 16:01.656
Yes, you do. This case
could end your career.

16:01.699 --> 16:04.789
If he destroys your reputation,
you might never recover.

16:04.833 --> 16:06.356
That's what's going on
with me.

16:06.400 --> 16:07.836
♪♪♪

16:13.798 --> 16:23.634
[ indistinct conversations ]

16:23.678 --> 16:25.680
Can I--

16:25.723 --> 16:26.594
Oh.

16:26.637 --> 16:28.204
That's kind. Thank you.

16:28.248 --> 16:30.119
Is there anything else
I can get you?

16:30.163 --> 16:32.121
Cup of tea or something?

16:32.165 --> 16:33.775
Shot of bourbon?

16:33.818 --> 16:36.473
I've just been trying
not to cry in there.

16:36.517 --> 16:39.302
All those people
looking at me all the time.

16:39.346 --> 16:41.130
None of their business.
[ sniffles ]

16:41.174 --> 16:42.479
[ elevator bell dings ]

16:42.523 --> 16:46.005
I still live in the same house
I was born in.

16:46.048 --> 16:48.007
Hayley was born there, too.

16:48.050 --> 16:52.098
Cookeville, Tennessee.
Putnam County.

16:52.141 --> 16:55.797
She loved horses.
[ laughs ]

16:55.840 --> 16:59.844
I don't know. Taylor Swift.
[ chuckles ]

16:59.888 --> 17:04.414
She had her problems,
but she was getting better.

17:04.458 --> 17:07.156
She was really trying.

17:07.200 --> 17:09.854
Last time we talked...

17:12.292 --> 17:14.685
The week before she died...

17:16.078 --> 17:19.473
She was planning
to come on home for a visit.

17:19.516 --> 17:21.953
She said...

17:21.997 --> 17:25.044
the problem with L.A...

17:25.087 --> 17:26.741
she could never sleep here.

17:29.178 --> 17:31.833
[ cries ] She couldn't ever
get a decent sleep.

17:39.580 --> 17:40.842
Emily:
You're scared. I get that.

17:40.885 --> 17:42.409
Your grandma is
definitely scary,

17:42.452 --> 17:44.063
but there are things
we can do

17:44.106 --> 17:46.108
to protect you in jail, okay?
We're gonna go upstairs,

17:46.152 --> 17:47.849
and you're gonna give
your statement to Mr. Callan.

17:47.892 --> 17:49.981
I can't do it, okay?
I'm sorry.Billy.

17:50.025 --> 17:52.723
You don't know her.
She will find me in jail.

17:52.767 --> 17:54.638
Billy, this is
an excellent deal.

17:54.682 --> 17:57.554
I'm not doing it, okay?
I can't do it. I can't flip.

17:57.598 --> 17:59.774
When we were kids,
she caught my cousin Benny

17:59.817 --> 18:02.081
sneaking cigarettes
from her purse.

18:02.124 --> 18:04.083
She took a hot iron,
like a clothes iron,

18:04.126 --> 18:06.955
and she burned his hand.
It's still all scarred.

18:10.045 --> 18:12.395
What if I can keep you
out of jail?

18:12.439 --> 18:14.136
Do you have any family
who aren't...

18:14.180 --> 18:17.139
Criminals?Is there anyone else
you could stay with?

18:17.183 --> 18:20.925
My mom's sister's a nurse,
lives up in Ferndale.

18:20.969 --> 18:23.406
Would you be safe there
if I can get you a new deal?

18:23.450 --> 18:26.453
Could you do that?
No jail?

18:26.496 --> 18:28.411
I can try.

18:28.455 --> 18:30.718
Lola:
Nice try, Mr. Pryce.

18:30.761 --> 18:32.459
I have reviewed the video.

18:32.502 --> 18:35.070
I find it to be more
prejudicial than probative.

18:35.114 --> 18:38.813
The victim's drug use is
already well established.

18:38.856 --> 18:42.643
The disclosure was untimely.
It will not be admitted,

18:42.686 --> 18:45.124
and a curative jury instruction
will be issued.

18:45.167 --> 18:46.168
Any questions?

18:46.212 --> 18:47.561
Not a one, Your Honor.
Thank you.

18:47.604 --> 18:49.563
Understood, Your Honor.

18:50.825 --> 18:52.870
Let's bring the jury back in.

18:54.916 --> 18:56.396
[ buzz ]

18:56.439 --> 18:57.484
Um...

18:57.527 --> 18:59.747
[ whispering indistinctly ]

19:01.879 --> 19:03.577
- Your Honor, if I may...
- Just a moment.

19:03.620 --> 19:06.797
After conferring with my client,
I must ask you to reconsider.

19:06.841 --> 19:08.973
- Mr. Pryce.
- The video clearly shows...

19:09.017 --> 19:10.845
- That is enough!
- ...Hayley high on heroin,

19:10.888 --> 19:14.109
[ door closes ]...being aggressive
and abusive towards my client,

19:14.153 --> 19:16.416
and I feel like...Mr. Pryce, you are
out of order.

19:16.459 --> 19:19.245
...to exclude it would be
to exclude the truth.Sit down and stop talking!

19:20.855 --> 19:23.597
Of course.[ gallery murmuring ]

19:23.640 --> 19:27.209
My apologies to the court.

19:27.253 --> 19:31.257
[ gallery murmuring ]

19:31.300 --> 19:34.042
The jury will disregard
that exchange.

19:34.085 --> 19:37.480
They will also disregard
the contents of the video,

19:37.524 --> 19:39.787
and it will be excluded
from the record.

19:39.830 --> 19:43.399
As always, our goal is justice.[ cellphone buzzes ]

19:43.443 --> 19:45.706
- And as such, we--
- I'm sorry. I--

19:45.749 --> 19:47.142
Your Honor, I need to...

19:48.752 --> 19:50.014
What is it?

19:50.058 --> 19:51.842
[ lowered voice ]
An Olivia fan account.

19:51.886 --> 19:53.322
Username LivFreeOrDieHard

19:53.366 --> 19:55.324
just posted photos
of the jury.[ cellphones buzzing ]

19:55.368 --> 19:57.065
This jury.

19:57.108 --> 19:59.633
[ gallery murmuring,
cellphones continue buzzing ]

19:59.676 --> 20:01.548
That was taken from our gallery.

20:01.591 --> 20:03.245
[ murmuring continues ]Order.

20:03.289 --> 20:04.594
[ gavel bangs ]

20:04.638 --> 20:06.596
This court
will come to order.

20:06.640 --> 20:07.902
[ gavel banging ]

20:07.945 --> 20:09.382
[ indistinct conversations ]

20:09.425 --> 20:11.210
They took a picture of the jury.
We need to find them.

20:11.253 --> 20:13.429
17 rooms,
and we'll need all televisions

20:13.473 --> 20:17.041
and phones removed
and absolutely no room service.

20:17.085 --> 20:18.826
The mob is trying
to crowdsource information

20:18.869 --> 20:21.698
on the jurors--
names, addresses.

20:21.742 --> 20:23.091
So you're going
to sequester them.

20:23.134 --> 20:24.484
I have no choice.

20:24.527 --> 20:26.268
I can't expect for them
to stay away from the news

20:26.312 --> 20:27.922
if they're
on the front page.

20:27.965 --> 20:30.838
That may be, but it's still
a logistical nightmare.

20:30.881 --> 20:32.187
Well, if it's an issue,

20:32.231 --> 20:33.667
we can take our business
to the DoubleTree.

20:33.710 --> 20:37.061
Mm.What about this case
isn't a nightmare?

20:37.105 --> 20:39.934
[ sighs ]
You know, Carmichael,

20:39.977 --> 20:41.979
you were fun to watch
as a prosecutor--

20:42.023 --> 20:44.068
a real fighter.
You'd take a hit,

20:44.112 --> 20:46.245
and you'd bounce back
with a knockout.

20:46.288 --> 20:48.203
It's a different kind of fight
once you put on the robe,

20:48.247 --> 20:50.336
but it's not that different.
You can handle this.

20:50.379 --> 20:51.554
Judge Benner's right.

20:51.598 --> 20:53.252
[ clatter ]

20:53.295 --> 20:55.123
Chin up, slugger.

20:57.081 --> 20:58.082
Slugger?

20:58.126 --> 20:59.562
Mark: Haven't we
done this already?

20:59.606 --> 21:01.825
- Callan, all I'm asking...
- I'm pretty sure we did.

21:01.869 --> 21:03.392
- My client is terrified.
- As was the clerk

21:03.436 --> 21:05.873
at the jewelry store
your client helped to rob.

21:05.916 --> 21:09.180
He's a 20-year-old kid.
You've met his grandmother.

21:09.224 --> 21:10.921
You've seen Kenny and Benny's
previous record.

21:10.965 --> 21:12.967
That's the kind of family
he grew up in.

21:13.010 --> 21:15.361
- Help me get him out.
- So we're doing that now.

21:15.404 --> 21:17.232
- What?
- Every attorney in your office

21:17.276 --> 21:19.365
has tried to play
the bad family card with me,

21:19.408 --> 21:21.018
thinking it would
strike a nerve or something.

21:21.062 --> 21:23.456
What are you t--
You think I--

21:23.499 --> 21:25.066
- Because of your father?
- Look.

21:25.109 --> 21:27.198
- You're--You're kidding, right?
- It's been known to happen.

21:27.242 --> 21:29.026
I would never use
your personal life

21:29.070 --> 21:33.030
to gain an advantage, especially
after what I told you,

21:33.074 --> 21:36.469
what I shared with you before.
I don't tell that to anyone.

21:36.512 --> 21:39.602
I refuse to let it--
that...

21:39.646 --> 21:41.300
himdefine me

21:41.343 --> 21:43.519
any more than your dad
or Billy's family

21:43.563 --> 21:45.347
should define you.

21:45.391 --> 21:47.349
You know what I mean.

21:49.220 --> 21:52.267
Benny and Kenny are suspects
in at least 10 other jobs.

21:52.311 --> 21:55.009
It depends
what Billy can offer.

21:55.052 --> 21:57.316
I'm on it. Thank you.

21:57.359 --> 21:59.143
Lopez.

21:59.187 --> 22:02.973
What you told me...
I would never say anything.

22:04.410 --> 22:06.107
I appreciate that.

22:06.150 --> 22:07.891
Thanks.

22:07.935 --> 22:09.850
[ telephone rings in distance ]

22:09.893 --> 22:11.852
Sherri:
You will have your own room,

22:11.895 --> 22:13.854
and you will be fed.

22:13.897 --> 22:16.465
You will have no contact
with the outside world,

22:16.509 --> 22:18.075
including phones.

22:18.119 --> 22:22.036
You will hand them
to Deputy Watkins as you exit.

22:22.079 --> 22:24.125
Hey, Deputy, I need
to make a small request.

22:24.168 --> 22:25.909
You got to talk
to the boss.

22:25.953 --> 22:27.955
No, I know, I know.
It's just she's a little...

22:29.870 --> 22:31.262
terrifying.

22:31.306 --> 22:35.266
It's my 20th
wedding anniversary today.

22:35.310 --> 22:37.312
Is there any way that I could
have dinner with my wife?

22:37.356 --> 22:40.228
You're sequestered.
It's against the rules.

22:41.969 --> 22:43.405
I guess if you didn't
discuss the case

22:43.449 --> 22:46.103
and if I was there
as, like, a chaperone,

22:46.147 --> 22:48.062
the judge mightallow it.

22:49.672 --> 22:51.413
[ chuckles ]

22:53.372 --> 22:56.766
[ sighs ]
Any more Che sightings?

22:56.810 --> 22:58.812
No. Everyone's too busy

22:58.855 --> 23:00.248
trying to figure out
which soap opera

23:00.291 --> 23:02.293
they recognize
juror number 7 from.

23:03.730 --> 23:05.471
[ sighs ]
I close my eyes,

23:05.514 --> 23:07.908
and all I can see is
Hayley in that video.

23:07.951 --> 23:09.518
That poor girl.

23:09.562 --> 23:12.565
I can't imagine if my mother had
to see something like that.

23:12.608 --> 23:14.393
I talked to the mom
at recess,

23:14.436 --> 23:15.698
and she's a sweetheart.

23:15.742 --> 23:17.439
She told me...

23:17.483 --> 23:19.528
What is it now?

23:19.572 --> 23:21.748
307 Parkhurst Avenue?

23:21.791 --> 23:24.054
That's my home address.

23:24.098 --> 23:28.102
Someone posted
my home address online?

23:28.145 --> 23:30.757
- Judge Carmichael.
- I know. I just found out.

23:30.800 --> 23:34.064
How bad is it?People are taking selfies
with your mailbox.

23:34.108 --> 23:36.415
Is your husband...Robin's in D.C.
until tomorrow.

23:36.458 --> 23:37.851
Going home is
out of the question.

23:37.894 --> 23:40.027
Do you have someplace else
you can stay?

23:40.070 --> 23:43.160
- Your parents? A friend?
- And if I'm followed? No.

23:43.204 --> 23:45.206
I'm not subjecting
anyone else to this.

23:45.249 --> 23:47.251
- I'll stay in a hotel.
- This is L.A.

23:47.295 --> 23:49.558
Every bellhop is going
to have TMZ on speed dial.

23:49.602 --> 23:50.820
She can stay with me.

23:52.953 --> 23:55.564
Thank you so much, Sherri,
but I am--

23:55.608 --> 23:57.218
That's a good idea.

23:57.261 --> 23:59.220
We need to know
where you are.

23:59.263 --> 24:01.222
Don't argue.

24:01.265 --> 24:02.528
♪♪♪

24:08.098 --> 24:09.012
[ door creaks, switch clicks ]

24:13.539 --> 24:16.237
Oh. This is a lovely home.[ door closes ]

24:16.280 --> 24:18.282
Please take off
your shoes.

24:21.895 --> 24:25.072
Guest bedroom is down the hall.
Bathroom is right next door.

24:25.115 --> 24:27.422
You'll find a fresh toothbrush
in the top drawer.

24:27.466 --> 24:29.076
If you would please wipe down
the counter in the morning.

24:29.119 --> 24:30.338
Of course.

24:31.818 --> 24:33.297
I spoke to the sheriff.

24:33.341 --> 24:37.171
There will be a car outside
24/7 here and at your house.

24:38.477 --> 24:40.217
The Taj Mahal. Have you been?

24:40.261 --> 24:41.654
Please don't help.
I have a system.

24:41.697 --> 24:45.005
I respect the system.
Totally respect the system.

24:45.048 --> 24:46.702
Drink this.

24:46.746 --> 24:50.140
- You're not having?
- I'll have one with dinner.

24:50.184 --> 24:53.100
Oh, my God. Is that you?

24:53.143 --> 24:55.145
Could you please
just not snoop?

24:55.189 --> 24:57.496
Sorry. You look good.

24:57.539 --> 25:00.020
Are you acting
with the puppet?

25:02.979 --> 25:04.546
Me as Che,
you with the puppet--

25:04.590 --> 25:06.156
the mob would have
a field day.

25:09.290 --> 25:10.247
- Sherri...
- Your Honor--

25:10.291 --> 25:11.858
...if this is
too uncomfortable...

25:11.901 --> 25:13.773
No. It's lovely.

25:13.816 --> 25:18.125
We haven't yet had social time.
We can check it off.

25:19.779 --> 25:22.390
[ glass clinks ]

25:22.433 --> 25:25.262
316.

25:25.306 --> 25:26.437
- Good night.
- 319.

25:26.481 --> 25:27.569
Thanks.

25:27.613 --> 25:31.225
And 323.
All right, that should be it.

25:31.268 --> 25:32.443
Everybody up to their rooms,
okay?

25:32.487 --> 25:35.925
Bedtime? It's 8:00,
and you have to study.

25:35.969 --> 25:37.144
Hey, you're here.

25:37.187 --> 25:39.189
I heard about the thing,
the jury.

25:39.233 --> 25:40.495
Thought you might
be stuck here,

25:40.539 --> 25:42.889
and I'm not gonna let you
fail your exams.

25:42.932 --> 25:44.281
Dug out my old flashcards.

25:44.325 --> 25:46.719
They are amazing.
You will be humbled.

25:46.762 --> 25:48.459
- [ clears throat ]
- What, scared?

25:48.503 --> 25:49.460
Of flashcards? No.
I just...

25:49.504 --> 25:51.419
- Then...
- I have a date.

25:51.462 --> 25:54.117
Oh. Sorry. I--
A date with who?

25:54.161 --> 25:56.598
No, no, no.
Juror number 5 and his wife.

25:56.642 --> 25:59.253
It's their 20th anniversary.
I have to chaperone.

25:59.296 --> 26:01.908
- It was the only way.
- Count me in. Table for four.

26:01.951 --> 26:04.040
I mean,
if that's cool with you.

26:04.084 --> 26:05.389
Just don't tell
Judge Carmichael.

26:05.433 --> 26:07.174
Secret's safe with me.

26:07.217 --> 26:08.523
[ elevator bell dings ]

26:08.567 --> 26:09.568
[ clears throat ]
Let me introduce you.

26:09.611 --> 26:11.526
Yeah.

26:17.488 --> 26:20.840
Pad Thai shrimp
and spring rolls.

26:20.883 --> 26:22.276
You brought me food?

26:22.319 --> 26:24.321
No big deal. I was getting
some for myself, and...

26:24.365 --> 26:26.585
I'm busy, Callan.
You want a favor? Which case?

26:26.628 --> 26:29.588
Billy Webb needs a new deal.
His grandma threatened him.

26:29.631 --> 26:33.679
His grandma.Kind of said she'd get him
shivved in prison.

26:33.722 --> 26:36.377
- I believe her.
- Okay, let's hear it.

26:36.420 --> 26:38.292
Three years probation,
credit time served.

26:38.335 --> 26:40.163
No contact with former
known associates,

26:40.207 --> 26:42.078
including his family.
- Good. Now go away.

26:42.122 --> 26:43.253
[ crunches ]

26:45.865 --> 26:49.172
Some judges are legal nerds,
some are bleeding hearts.

26:49.216 --> 26:51.392
Lola's both.
Razor-sharp on case law,

26:51.435 --> 26:53.829
and she always sees
the human being behind the case.

26:53.873 --> 26:56.223
She'll respect you
if you can do both.

26:57.659 --> 26:59.879
The victim's mother.

26:59.922 --> 27:02.403
I can feel her eyes on me.

27:02.446 --> 27:05.449
Yeah. Like a tingling
on the back of your neck?

27:05.493 --> 27:07.016
Tomorrow she's gonna watch

27:07.060 --> 27:08.583
her daughter's killer
take the stand.

27:08.627 --> 27:11.673
Pryce is putting up Olivia?

27:11.717 --> 27:15.634
If you need a test audience
for your cross...

27:16.983 --> 27:19.202
I'm here. [ crunches ]

27:23.293 --> 27:25.295
♪♪♪

27:25.339 --> 27:26.862
[ glasses clink ]

27:26.906 --> 27:31.432
[ both chuckle ]

27:32.738 --> 27:36.393
This is awkward.
I know. I'm sorry.

27:36.437 --> 27:39.701
- No, no. It's okay.
- We get it. We're grateful.

27:39.745 --> 27:41.311
Why don't you tell us
how you met?

27:41.355 --> 27:44.750
I mean, 20 years--
that's impressive.

27:44.793 --> 27:47.578
- When did you know?
- Okay, well, Hank here--

27:47.622 --> 27:49.755
- Don't tell us his name.
- Oh. I'm sorry.

27:49.798 --> 27:52.888
Juror number 5--
which I love, by the way...

27:52.932 --> 27:55.935
- That's gonna become a thing.
- Okay.

27:55.978 --> 27:58.938
Juror number 5 was new in town.

27:58.981 --> 28:00.722
I was living
in New York,

28:00.766 --> 28:03.725
and I came out here
'cause, you know, L.A.

28:03.769 --> 28:05.553
- [ chuckles ]
- He was bartending.

28:05.596 --> 28:07.381
I get my first paycheck,
and I go to the bank.

28:07.424 --> 28:08.817
And I was his teller.

28:08.861 --> 28:09.862
- Right.
- I love it.

28:09.905 --> 28:11.298
No way.

28:11.341 --> 28:14.083
Bam. The second
I saw that smile,

28:14.127 --> 28:16.956
- I knew.
- Took me a bit longer.

28:16.999 --> 28:18.479
Yeah, like six months.

28:18.522 --> 28:22.831
I had just split from my ex.
But number 5 knew.

28:22.875 --> 28:24.659
He always knew.

28:24.703 --> 28:27.793
I figured if I could just
see that smile every day,

28:27.836 --> 28:30.970
I could figure the rest out,
you know?

28:31.013 --> 28:36.105
♪♪♪

28:36.149 --> 28:38.194
You two?
How long have you...

28:38.238 --> 28:41.110
Oh. I mean, it's not...
We just--

28:41.154 --> 28:42.982
- We're just friends.
- Mm-hmm.

28:43.025 --> 28:44.026
Work friends.

28:44.070 --> 28:45.375
- Mm-hmm.
- Friends.

28:45.419 --> 28:48.204
Yeah. Right.

28:48.248 --> 28:49.423
Right.

28:49.466 --> 28:50.685
[ whispers ] Yeah.

28:50.729 --> 28:53.383
[ chuckling ]
My parents were...

28:53.427 --> 28:55.690
I guess you could
call them hippies.

28:55.734 --> 28:58.911
Kind of a surfer-hippie
hybrid in the '90s,

28:58.954 --> 29:00.651
which is ridiculous.

29:00.695 --> 29:03.176
They lived on the beach
at Big Sur.

29:03.219 --> 29:04.743
They smoked pot.

29:04.786 --> 29:08.398
They did not believe
in rules or college.

29:08.442 --> 29:10.052
- Wow.
- 15 years old.

29:10.096 --> 29:13.099
I'm working at
the Seafood Shack in Monterey,

29:13.142 --> 29:14.796
trying to save up
for school.

29:14.840 --> 29:16.798
And my parents are
in their 40s

29:16.842 --> 29:18.365
and dropping acid.

29:18.408 --> 29:20.846
They come into my work
and run up a $200 tab

29:20.889 --> 29:24.545
and leave without paying.
I got fired on the spot.

29:24.588 --> 29:28.070
Next day, I left home.

29:28.114 --> 29:31.073
That is so awful.

29:31.117 --> 29:34.424
♪♪♪

29:34.468 --> 29:36.557
20 years later,
I am obsessed

29:36.600 --> 29:42.215
with boundaries
and order and control.

29:42.258 --> 29:44.347
♪♪♪

29:44.391 --> 29:46.567
Men like Adam Pryce--

29:46.610 --> 29:50.092
the chaos they bring,
like a swarm of flies.

29:50.136 --> 29:53.008
Everything is a story.
Everything needs to be spun.

29:53.052 --> 29:56.272
My problem, Your Honor,
is that you--

29:56.316 --> 29:59.014
you've become a character
in his drama.

29:59.058 --> 30:00.407
Pryce made you the villain,

30:00.450 --> 30:03.758
and as long as you are
the baddie, Olivia isn't.

30:03.802 --> 30:06.587
Sherri, the jury hasn't
rendered its verdict yet.

30:06.630 --> 30:09.677
I can control the courtroom.
Most of the time,

30:09.720 --> 30:11.897
despite your efforts
to thwart me.

30:11.940 --> 30:14.421
But I can't control
the internet or the media.

30:14.464 --> 30:16.292
I can't control
Adam Pryce,

30:16.336 --> 30:18.817
which means
I can't protect you,

30:18.860 --> 30:20.775
Your Honor.

30:20.819 --> 30:23.169
I'm 15 again,
standing in a restaurant

30:23.212 --> 30:27.347
while my world collapses
around me.

30:27.390 --> 30:29.871
[ cellphone chimes ]

30:29.915 --> 30:32.656
It's Judge Benner.

30:34.528 --> 30:37.270
The video of Hayley--
it got leaked.

30:37.313 --> 30:38.662
Enough.

30:40.447 --> 30:42.275
He's beating you.
Don't let him.

30:42.318 --> 30:44.625
- What exactly--
- What Judge Benner said.

30:44.668 --> 30:46.453
It is a different fight
now that you're a judge.

30:46.496 --> 30:48.934
Don't argue with him.
Control him.

30:48.977 --> 30:52.111
I already threatened contempt,
and he didn't blink.

30:52.154 --> 30:53.895
Fight fire with fire.

30:53.939 --> 30:56.115
Bullies like Pryce
thrive on fear,

30:56.158 --> 30:58.857
so what scares him?

31:01.947 --> 31:05.037
Call Sara right now.
Tell her I need a transcript.

31:05.080 --> 31:07.517
♪♪♪

31:14.002 --> 31:18.354
[ indistinct conversations ]

31:18.398 --> 31:21.140
Big day.
Olivia's taking the stand.

31:21.183 --> 31:24.795
I'm guessing Chanel shift dress
with a tasteful cardigan?

31:24.839 --> 31:26.928
You think I'd allow her
to repeat an outfit?

31:26.972 --> 31:28.843
Oh, God, no, you wouldn't.

31:28.887 --> 31:30.932
Can I help you
with something?

31:30.976 --> 31:32.629
[ exhales deeply ]
Sorry. No.

31:34.327 --> 31:36.895
I just thought
you might like to know

31:36.938 --> 31:40.420
they're relocating the trial.
Airport courthouse.

31:40.463 --> 31:42.378
They want to thin down
the crowd.

31:42.422 --> 31:43.989
You didn't hear it from me,

31:44.032 --> 31:46.382
but the judge will announce it
this afternoon.

31:46.426 --> 31:47.993
Oh. And just a heads up.

31:48.036 --> 31:51.997
The lighting there will
really make pastels pop.

31:52.040 --> 31:55.870
[ indistinct conversations ]

31:55.914 --> 31:58.742
[ voice breaking ]
It was so, so awful.

31:58.786 --> 32:00.005
I was paralyzed.

32:00.048 --> 32:02.268
I mean, Hayley was, um,

32:02.311 --> 32:04.574
she was pale, almost blue,

32:04.618 --> 32:08.491
and her stomach was
doing all this, um...

32:08.535 --> 32:09.928
it was heaving.

32:09.971 --> 32:11.407
[ sobbing ]

32:11.451 --> 32:14.584
But if I had called
for help...

32:14.628 --> 32:17.326
if I had exposed
her addiction...

32:19.328 --> 32:20.677
...she would have
killed me.

32:20.721 --> 32:23.245
- Objection. Speculation.
- Sustained.

32:23.289 --> 32:25.944
And how did that
make you feel, Olivia?

32:25.987 --> 32:27.771
Terrified.

32:27.815 --> 32:29.512
- In fear for my life.
- Objection.

32:29.556 --> 32:31.166
The feelings and impressions
of my client...

32:31.210 --> 32:33.908
Both of you, approach.Your Honor,
with all due respect--

32:33.952 --> 32:36.084
Respect is precisely
what this court is due.

32:36.128 --> 32:39.435
If you have more evidence
to present, then proceed.

32:39.479 --> 32:41.002
But if your behavior
doesn't--

32:41.046 --> 32:42.264
My behavior?!

32:42.308 --> 32:44.701
My behavior has been
unimpeachable!

32:44.745 --> 32:46.138
I wonder if the State Bar
would agree.

32:46.181 --> 32:47.791
I beg your pardon?

32:47.835 --> 32:50.229
This is a complaint
to the State Bar

32:50.272 --> 32:51.621
detailing
the attorney misconduct

32:51.665 --> 32:53.493
I have witnessed
during these proceedings.

32:53.536 --> 32:54.798
- [ scoffs ]
- Improper trial publicity,

32:54.842 --> 32:57.279
recklessly
maligning the court,

32:57.323 --> 32:58.585
conduct prejudicial

32:58.628 --> 33:00.239
to the administration
of justice,

33:00.282 --> 33:02.850
just to name a few.
- Your Honor, on what basis--

33:02.893 --> 33:06.810
And this is a full transcript
of these proceedings,

33:06.854 --> 33:09.291
everything you've done,
every word you've said.

33:09.335 --> 33:10.814
Are you prepared

33:10.858 --> 33:13.121
to defend your behavior
to the State Bar,

33:13.165 --> 33:14.731
to put your license
on the line?

33:14.775 --> 33:16.951
Because I am prepared
to file this complaint.

33:16.995 --> 33:20.041
Or perhaps you'd be willing
to follow the law,

33:20.085 --> 33:22.913
to show respect
for thisprocess,

33:22.957 --> 33:26.265
to give your clientthe defense
to which she is entitled.

33:26.308 --> 33:28.441
Mr. Pryce,
it's entirely up to you.

33:28.484 --> 33:34.664
[ gallery murmuring ]

33:36.623 --> 33:38.494
Any other threats you'd like
to make, Your Honor,

33:38.538 --> 33:40.453
or may I resume?

33:40.496 --> 33:43.891
By all means. Step back.

33:53.118 --> 33:55.555
Ms. McLeland...

33:55.598 --> 33:57.861
did you kill
Hayley Halliwell?

33:57.905 --> 33:59.385
Of course not.

33:59.428 --> 34:02.431
Nothing further, Your Honor.

34:05.173 --> 34:06.870
It's your cross,
Mr. Choi.

34:10.352 --> 34:12.006
Here's what
we can offer you--

34:12.050 --> 34:13.747
break-ins at two
auto part shops in Van Nuys

34:13.790 --> 34:15.357
and a bank in Reseda.

34:15.401 --> 34:17.142
Really? A bank?

34:17.185 --> 34:19.274
Billy didn't take part, but he
witnessed the preparations

34:19.318 --> 34:21.755
and the return.It was kind of a bust.
30 grand.

34:21.798 --> 34:23.496
- Benny and Kenny were pissed.
- I want to emphasize

34:23.539 --> 34:25.106
that my client has never
carried a weapon

34:25.150 --> 34:27.891
or hurt anyone.
He was at best a junior--

34:27.935 --> 34:29.023
Three years probation,
time served.

34:29.067 --> 34:30.546
No contact
with his family here.

34:30.590 --> 34:31.547
- Sold.
- Billy.

34:31.591 --> 34:34.550
- Sorry.
- Sold.

34:34.594 --> 34:36.030
Thank you.

34:36.074 --> 34:39.033
There are other families
out there, Billy,

34:39.077 --> 34:40.165
all kinds of families.

34:40.208 --> 34:43.081
You should find one
that respects you.

34:43.124 --> 34:45.909
Let's go
before he changes his mind.

34:45.953 --> 34:48.390
- As if I would ever.
- He does it constantly,

34:48.434 --> 34:51.698
many, many times.

34:51.741 --> 34:53.439
[ indistinct conversations ]

34:55.745 --> 34:58.096
This is a post that was made
to your Instagram account.

34:58.139 --> 35:00.750
- Yes.
- You and Hayley, May 11th,

35:00.794 --> 35:04.145
just a couple of hours
before Hayley died.

35:04.189 --> 35:06.582
Yes. Things were bad,

35:06.626 --> 35:09.629
but I had to put on
a brave face for the fans.

35:09.672 --> 35:11.283
So you were intentionally
misrepresenting

35:11.326 --> 35:12.414
your relationship
with Hayley.

35:12.458 --> 35:14.329
- That's your story?
- Objection!

35:14.373 --> 35:15.504
He's embellishing
the testimony.

35:15.548 --> 35:17.637
Overruled.
The witness will answer.

35:19.378 --> 35:21.162
Yes. I had to
for the fans.

35:21.206 --> 35:23.251
It was just the two of you
at the house.

35:23.295 --> 35:24.600
Yes.

35:24.644 --> 35:25.906
The medical examiner
testified

35:25.949 --> 35:27.908
that Hayley had bruises
on her wrists

35:27.951 --> 35:30.040
consistent with someone
restraining her

35:30.084 --> 35:31.694
while the dose
was injected.

35:31.738 --> 35:34.044
He also said that they
could have happened earlier,

35:34.088 --> 35:35.437
some other way.

35:35.481 --> 35:36.612
Is there a question,
Your Honor?

35:36.656 --> 35:38.440
There is.

35:38.484 --> 35:40.138
Olivia...

35:40.181 --> 35:43.184
are there any bruises
on Hayley's wrist

35:43.228 --> 35:45.055
in this photograph

35:45.099 --> 35:47.406
taken mere hours
before Hayley's death?

35:47.449 --> 35:49.234
- Objection!
- Overruled.

35:49.277 --> 35:55.109
[ gallery murmuring ]

35:55.153 --> 35:57.807
There are no bruises,
and you're the only one

35:57.851 --> 36:00.201
who was with her
before she died.

36:00.245 --> 36:01.811
You seized your chance.

36:01.855 --> 36:03.639
She caught you stealing,
and so you killed her.

36:03.683 --> 36:07.077
You don't understand.

36:07.121 --> 36:09.384
She had it all,

36:09.428 --> 36:11.473
and she was
throwing it away,

36:11.517 --> 36:13.171
one fix at a time.

36:13.214 --> 36:16.130
Do you know how it felt
watching that?

36:16.174 --> 36:19.220
Hayley said she was going
to call the police,

36:19.264 --> 36:20.874
and I would have...

36:20.917 --> 36:22.528
[ gallery murmuring ]

36:22.571 --> 36:25.052
And you would have what?

36:25.095 --> 36:27.097
Gone to jail?

36:27.141 --> 36:29.230
So you had to act.

36:29.274 --> 36:31.537
"As to count 1 of violation

36:31.580 --> 36:34.017
"of Penal Code Section 187
Subdivision "A,"

36:34.061 --> 36:36.542
"murder in the first degree,
we find the defendant...

36:36.585 --> 36:37.673
guilty."

36:37.717 --> 36:39.327
[ gallery gasps and murmurs ]

36:39.371 --> 36:42.025
Sentencing will be
two weeks from today's date.

36:42.069 --> 36:44.071
The defendant is remanded
into custody without bail.

36:44.114 --> 36:45.899
[ gasps ][ handcuffs click ]

36:45.942 --> 36:47.814
Ladies and gentlemen
of the jury,

36:47.857 --> 36:49.729
thank you for your service.
You are dismissed.

36:49.772 --> 36:51.513
Court is adjourned.

36:51.557 --> 36:53.428
All rise.

36:53.472 --> 36:56.736
[ gallery murmuring ]

37:08.313 --> 37:10.837
What does our calendar
look like for tomorrow?

37:10.880 --> 37:13.709
You're backed up, obviously.
It's gonna be a nightmare,

37:13.753 --> 37:15.842
which you no doubt
will only make worse.

37:23.197 --> 37:25.243
♪♪♪

37:25.286 --> 37:26.069
[ door closes ]

37:26.113 --> 37:36.123
♪♪♪

37:36.166 --> 37:46.220
♪♪♪

37:46.220 --> 37:53.488
♪♪♪

37:53.532 --> 37:54.837
Guess Olivia
won't be needing

37:54.881 --> 37:57.144
all those fancy clothes
anymore.

37:57.187 --> 37:59.973
Was it worth it,
the exposure?

38:00.016 --> 38:02.410
My phone won't stop
ringing, so yeah.

38:02.454 --> 38:04.934
Just growing your brand.

38:04.978 --> 38:07.546
Try that on the sheriff
when he calls.

38:07.589 --> 38:09.156
Excuse me?

38:09.199 --> 38:10.679
Posting pictures of jurors
is a felony.

38:10.723 --> 38:12.377
No idea
how that involves me.

38:12.420 --> 38:14.814
The same account that tweeted
those jury photos

38:14.857 --> 38:17.295
also posted a crazy rumor
this morning

38:17.338 --> 38:19.122
that things were moving
to the airport courthouse.

38:19.166 --> 38:20.950
You're the one
that told me that the--

38:20.994 --> 38:22.822
And you were
the only person I told,

38:22.865 --> 38:25.781
which I mentioned

38:25.825 --> 38:27.609
when I spoke
with the sheriff's office.

38:27.653 --> 38:29.568
Oh, but don't worry.

38:29.611 --> 38:33.311
I mean, you of all people
can rock those prison blues.

38:33.354 --> 38:43.886
♪♪♪

38:47.803 --> 38:49.109
[ door closes ]

38:49.152 --> 38:50.893
Sorry, Judge.
Almost done here.

38:50.937 --> 38:53.635
I got to hit the road if I'm
gonna make my reservation.

38:53.679 --> 38:55.376
Vespertine. Tasting menu.

38:55.420 --> 38:59.598
What about you?
Any fun post-trial plans?

38:59.641 --> 39:02.252
Oh, I'll probably
just kick back,

39:02.296 --> 39:04.646
brainstorm new ways
to--what was it?

39:04.690 --> 39:05.995
Muzzle justice?

39:06.039 --> 39:07.606
I hope you didn't take that
too personally.

39:07.649 --> 39:09.172
Does the truth
even matter to you?

39:09.216 --> 39:11.827
Your Honor, we both know the
only truth is best story wins.

39:11.871 --> 39:14.917
- [ sighs ]
- All this--it's only theater.

39:17.311 --> 39:19.835
Nope. No, no, no.

39:19.879 --> 39:21.707
[ laughs ] You don't get
to be glib about this.

39:21.750 --> 39:23.317
In the theater,
the curtain drops,

39:23.361 --> 39:25.711
and people get to go
back to their own lives.

39:25.754 --> 39:27.669
Hayley Halliwell
doesn't get to do that.

39:27.713 --> 39:29.323
Now neither does your client.

39:29.367 --> 39:31.673
This is a place
where people come

39:31.717 --> 39:34.154
after something horrible
has happened

39:34.197 --> 39:36.809
to find out the truth.
- Your Honor, the truth--

39:36.852 --> 39:38.071
The truth that is discovered

39:38.114 --> 39:41.553
after a rigorous examination
of the facts.

39:41.596 --> 39:44.991
The facts need a story
to make sense.

39:45.034 --> 39:47.559
I am in the end
ethically obligated

39:47.602 --> 39:50.518
to provide zealous advocacy
on my clients' behalf.

39:50.562 --> 39:54.000
What about your other
obligations? What about justice?

39:54.043 --> 39:57.220
Justice is a marble statue
wearing a blindfold.

39:57.264 --> 40:00.441
My clients are human,
flesh and blood.

40:00.485 --> 40:01.747
And on balance,

40:01.790 --> 40:03.705
they're always gonna be
more important to me.

40:03.749 --> 40:07.405
You know, I actually think
that you usedto believe that.

40:07.448 --> 40:10.190
- Used to?
- Well, it's, I don't know,

40:10.233 --> 40:12.714
maybe a tough sell
coming from a man

40:12.758 --> 40:15.064
talking about tasting menus

40:15.108 --> 40:18.111
while his client is boarding
the bus to L.A. County.

40:19.765 --> 40:21.941
I've enjoyed this,
Your Honor.

40:24.639 --> 40:27.381
We should do it again.

40:27.425 --> 40:30.079
[ door opens ]

40:32.778 --> 40:34.344
[ sighs ]

40:34.388 --> 40:36.346
I think
I was atthis party.

40:36.390 --> 40:38.697
Seriously, how do you
keep getting back here?

40:38.740 --> 40:40.263
A hidden passage,
secret staircase?

40:40.307 --> 40:42.091
Didn't I go
as John Dillinger?

40:42.135 --> 40:44.224
I seem to remember
pinstripes.

40:44.267 --> 40:46.095
I'm pretty sure
it was Beetlejuice.

40:46.139 --> 40:48.837
Robin texted.
He just got home.

